titleInfo.title: USA v. Taylor
titleInfo.subTitle: PRELIMINARY ORDER OF FORFEITURE- The United States' Amended Motion for Issuance of Preliminary Order of Forfeiture (Filing No. 24) is hereby granted, and the United States' Motion for Issuance of Preliminary Order of Forfeiture (Filing No. 23) is denied as moot. Based upon the Forfeiture Allegation of the Indictment and the Defendant's plea of guilty, the United States is hereby authorized to seize the following properties: 1. $4,037 in United States Currency; 2. Silver Sony Laptop Computer, Model #PCG3A4L; 3. Black iPhone IV Cell Phone, Model A1349; 4. Black Samsung Metro PCS Cell Phone, Model SCH-R910,the Defendant's interest in said properties is hereby forfeited to the United States for disposition. Upon adjudication of all third-party interests, this Court will enter a Final Order of Forfeiture pursuant to 18 U.S.C. ' 2428, in which all interests will be addressed as to Keno C. Taylor (1). Ordered by Chief Judge Laurie Smith Camp. (1 Certified copy to USM)( MKR)

titleInfo.title: USA v. Taylor
titleInfo.subTitle: FINAL ORDER OF FORFEITURE granting the Plaintiff's 29 Motion for Final Forfeiture as to Keno C. Taylor (1). All right, title and interest in and to the following property held by any person or entity are hereby forever barred and foreclosed. $4,037.00 in United States currency; Silver Sony Laptop Computer, Model #PCG3A4L; Black iPhone IV Cell Phone, Model A1349 ; Black Samsung Metro PCS Cell Phone, Model SCH-R910; The aforementioned property be, and the same hereby are, forfeited to the United States of America; and The United States is directed to dispose of said property in accordance with law. Ordered by Chief Judge Laurie Smith Camp. (1 Certified copy to USM)( MKR)
